Class DNA

java.lang.Object
DNA
public class DNA extends Object
A holding class for constants to represent the DNA bases: A, T, C and G. Note that values are assigned such that A and T are binary complements of each other and so are C and G. This simplifies some of the processing of DNA sequences.
Author:
amit
